From a skeptical perspective, SZA's music has a few potential downsides:  1. **Focus on Insecurities and Relationship Issues**: Her themes often dwell on self-doubt and troubled relationships, which could lead listeners to fixate on their own insecurities.    2. **Reinforcement of Negative Emotions**: The melancholic tone of her music might cause some listeners to stay in a low-energy, emotional state.  3. **Romanticization of Toxic Behavior**: Certain songs touch on toxic dynamics, which could be seen as normalizing or even glamorizing unhealthy relationships.  4. **Overemphasis on Personal Dramas**: The focus on inner conflict could lead some to feel trapped in personal issues rather than encouraging personal growth.  5. **Repetitive Themes**: Constant focus on heartbreak and doubt may feel limited or uninspiring to some.   These elements may impact listeners differently, depending on individual perspectives and needs.

This song talks about mental health and the toxicity that surrounds us daily and how we should face it. I wrote a first verse: It introduces the feeling of seeking fresh air and mental freedom, contrasting with the presence of heavy thoughts and the desire to push them away. 2. Second verse: Expresses the Third verse: Describes the feeling of being in an internal battle to free oneself from emotional weight and find peace, while observing the world around them fall apart. 4. Fourth verse: Portrays the determination to resist fear and limitations, and the desire to free oneself and feel like a winner, despite the difficulties. 5. Fourth verse: Portrays the determination to resist fear and limitations, and the desire to free oneself and feel like a winner, despite the difficulties. 5. Fifth verse: Talks about the desire to find mental serenity before it's too late, and the decision not to hold onto the past or regrets.  The song explores themes of self-acceptance, internal struggle, emotional freedom, and the pursuit of better days, even in the face of life's adversities.

As a 21 year old black man.....people always run with the stereotype of us bobbing our heads to gangsta and mumble rap without even giving other genres a second look. If you are caught listening to anything other than that, you are considered weird or an outcast. Well hey....let me be an outcast. My Dad used to play so much old school and oldies music that I pretty much became an "old head" when it comes to music. I value the vocals of songs, the instrumental of songs, and the unique setup of songs. I religiously listen to the likes of SZA, Jhene Aiko, Arianna Grande, Doja Cat, you name it. Call it what you want but I genuinely enjoy their music. This is by far one of my most favorite SZA songs of all time. Such a beautiful song and message.

SZA's "Good Days" is audible medicine with relatable lyrics that oscillate profoundly, often mirroring my very own past life experiences. I appreciate her vulnerability, highlighting the defenseless ebb and flows of life's vicious unpredictability, meanwhile reminding us that there's no need to chase the fountains of youth because it's literally in the present. Such a grounding and blessed reminder.   Even her reference to Jericho and Job is a good reminder of the spirit withstanding all the many lessons in life, and still mustering the strength to trust yourself and not lose your shit. (Hi Strategy & Authority, lol)  I'll never grow tired of this song. It's a melodic sonnet that always aligns me in a reflective mode to honor my overall evolution in this continuum, as she continues to serenade me with the guided meditation to remain "...sunny inside, good day living in my mind."  Forward & Upward, love muffins. #randomosity

I wonder at the significance of the library and mushroom set? Like, obviously, she took shrooms and is going on a trip and envisioning herself in a little mushroom kingdom. I just think its interesting that both sets look like something out of a kids tv show that you would've seen in the mid to late 90's, ESPECIALLY that library set which gave me some serious Between The Lions/reading show for kids that were super popular during that time. And in the middle of all that is her. It's magical to see her as she is, a beautiful woman in all of her power and femininity, juxtaposing herself against what looks like things that could've been from her childhood. Then the song itself is a meditation on growing and developing as a person while looking for that soundness of mind -- accepting that chasing that feeling of youth or being young is pointless, especially when it's always going to be in your present. You as you are. SZA as she is. Those dances lend to that message by looking both graceful, freeing, and spontaneous. Was mesmerized!

10 of the World's Funniest One Liners  1. The hardness of butter is directly proportional to the softness of the bread. 2. The last thing on earth you want to do will be the last thing you do. 3. Diplomacy is the art of letting someone else get your way. 4. If ignorance is bliss, then tourists are in a constant state of euphoria. 5. If at first you don't succeed, don't try skydiving. 6. If Barbie is so popular, why do you have to buy her friends? 7. Stop repeat offenders. Don't re-elect them! 8. I intend to live forever. So far so good. 9. Who is "General Failure" and why is he reading my hard disk? 10. What happens if you get scared half to death twice?   Editorial: Probably the most thought-provoking one-liner is "Eat right. Stay fit. Die anyway." It's sad but true -- no matter what you do, you will die. This is because you have sinned against God. Let's see if that's true: Have you ever lied (even once)? Ever stolen (anything)? Jesus said, "Whoever looks upon a woman to lust after her, has committed adultery already with her in his heart." Ever looked with lust? If you have said "Yes" to these three questions, by your own admission, you are a lying, thieving, adulterer at heart; and we've only looked at three of the Ten Commandments. How will you do on Judgment Day? Will you be innocent or guilty? You know that you will be guilty, and end up in Hell. That's not God's will. He provided a way for you to be forgiven. He sent His Son to take your punishment: "God commended His love toward us, in that, while we were yet sinners, Christ died for us." Jesus then rose from the dead and defeated death. God promises everlasting life to all those who confess and forsake their sins, and trust in Jesus Christ. Please do that today . . . you may not have tomorrow. See John 14:21 for a wonderful promise. Then read the Bible daily and obey what you read. God will never let you down.
Number 15: Burger king foot lettuce. The last thing you want on your Burger King burger is someone's foot fungus, but as it turns out, that might be what you get. A 4channer uploaded a photo anonymously to the site showcasing his feet in a plastic bin of lettuce, with the statement: "This is the lettuce you eat at Burger King." Admittedly, he had shoes on but, that's even worse. The post went live at 11:38PM on July 16 and a mere 20 minutes later, the Burger King in question was alerted to the rogue employee. at least, I hope he's rogue. How did it happen? Well, the BK employee hadn't removed the Exif data from the uploaded photo, which suggested the culprit was somewhere in Mayfield Heights, Ohio. This was at @. 3 minutes later, at @, the Burger King branch address was posted, with wishes of happy unemployment. 5 minutes later, the news station was contacted by another 4channer. And 3 minutes later, at @, a link was posted. Bk's "Tell Us About US" online form. The foot photo otherwise known as Exhibit A, was attached. Cleveland Scene Magazine contacted the BK in question the next day. When questioned, the breakfast shift manager said, "Oh, I know who that is. He's getting fired." Mystery, Solved, by 4chan, now we can all go back to eating our fast food in peace.

this video makes no sense but I still love sza lol
I think its dope how this song was already stuck in my mind because it plays at the end of the "Hit Different" video. It almost felt like an interlude... or a complete switch-up that was part of how "Hit Different" ends. One song, completely different arrangements. Artists are doing that a lot nowadays... complete switch-ups in the same song. I Love the creativity that SZA brings. Sonically... visually. She's dope. In an era where so many artists sound like one another... its always great to see a real one breakthrough and put some real art in front of the masses. Her melodies are never forced... never feels like she's tryna write a HIT... nothing is too neat or manufactured. She's mastered the art of improv'ing / adlibbing melodies... sounds like she records the first melodies that hit her as she's jamming / vibing to the music... those natural melodies are usually not what gets kept... usually a writer has to adjust or tweak them to sound how they want... but her natural vibe is dope enough to vibe to. When you mesh that with the right production, it just makes the music addictive without being overly repetitive. I Love it. SZA is a whole vibe and a half. Great artist.

Death, it's one of the biggest events that will ever take place in your life. We face death everyday, conscious or unconsciously of it; death lurks around every corner of our life. Like a lion waiting to catch its prey, death comes for us all in many shapes and form; seemingly there is no one who can escape from the jaws of death. But did you know there is a reason why we die? The idea of death you're familiar with is only the tip of the iceberg. See we die because we've sinned against God. Death according to the bible is wages " for the wages of sin is death " (Romans 6:23). Because man sinned against God, we live in a fallen world, it was once perfect, but now in ruins. Now that sin exists, God is coming to judge the world In righteousness. "It's appointed a man once to die and after this judgement" (Hebrews 9:27) The standard he'll judge you by is the 10 commandments, God's moral law. He's so serious about sin that he gave anyone who sins the death sentence, the bible says you've earned it through sinning against God and God pays you in death. each time you sin you build up his wrath. â€œThe soul who sins shall die.â€ (Ezekiel 18:4) The punishment is the eternal fires of Hell " Where there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth" (Matthew 13:42) You will have to face God on Judgement Day. (Have you made a god in your mind that you're more comfortable with, a god to suit yourself?)  3.You shall not take God's name in vain. (Have you ever used God's holy Name as a cuss word?)  4.Remember the Sabbath Day, to keep it holy.  5.Honor your father and mother.  6. You shall not murder. (God considers hatred to be as murder, 1 John 3:15).  7. You shall not commit adultery. ("Whoever looks upon a woman to lust after her has committed adultery with her already in his heart" Matthew 5:27-28; this also includes sex before marriage).  8. You shall not steal. (Have you ever stolen anything? the value of the item is irrelevant).  9. You shall not lie. (Have you lied even once? Including answering these questions).  10. You shall not covet. (Have you ever jealously desired what belongs to others?)  James 2:10 says, â€œthe person who keeps all of the laws except one is as guilty as a person who has broken all of Godâ€™s laws.â€Â   The Bible says that God will punish all murderers, rapists, thieves, liars, adulterers, etc. He will even judge our words and thoughts.  If you have done any of those things, God sees you as guilty of breaking His law and the Bible warns that the guilty will end up in Hell. Will YOU be guilty on Judgement Day?Â   "For the wages of sin is death, but the gift of God is eternal life in Christ Jesus our Lord." (Romans 6:23)  God sent His Son to suffer and die on the cross. Jesus took the punishment upon Himself and defeated death on the cross; not because your Good but because God is rich in mercy.  â€œFor God so loved the world that He gave His only Son, whoever believes in Him should not perish but have eternal life.â€ (John 3:16)  Jesus rose from the dead and defeated death. Pray something like this:  "Dear God, today I turn away from all of my sins (name them). This day I put my trust in Jesus Christ as my Lord and Savior. He is the only way for me to be saved. As per usual, SZA's visuals are crazy.  She starts out being a mushroom. Mushrooms can form miles and miles of "roots", making them one of the most firmly planted beings on the planet, immobile and inextricably bound, like SZA feels about the idea that she's wasted her "Good Days" in an unfruitful relationship. As she starts to realize that her youth (best part of her, as she feels) wasn't wasted in the relationship, she progressively breaks free and starts dancing wildly, the ultimate expression of liberation; she's putting the fun in fungi lol.
